OSCP METHODOLOGY - IDENTIFYING AND EXPLOITING UNKNOWN VULNERABILITIES
STEP 1 - IDENTIFY THE SOFTWARE AND VERSION
When you find a web page or service, always ask "what is this running?"

Check the page title
Check the login page for version numbers
Check HTTP response headers: curl -I http://TARGET
Check page source for version info
Check /readme.txt, /changelog.txt, /license.txt

STEP 2 - GOOGLE IT
Search for:

"SOFTWARE NAME exploit"
"SOFTWARE NAME vulnerability"
"SOFTWARE NAME CVE"
"SOFTWARE NAME VERSION exploit"
Example: "UniFi Network Controller 6.4.54 exploit"

STEP 3 - SEARCHSPLOIT
searchsploit unifi
searchsploit "unifi network"
searchsploit apache 2.4.29
searchsploit openssh 8.1
To copy an exploit to your current directory:
searchsploit -m 45233
STEP 4 - CHECK EXPLOIT-DB ONLINE
Go to https://exploit-db.com
Search the software name and version
Download PoC code directly
STEP 5 - CHECK HACKTRICKS
Website: https://book.hacktricks.xyz
Google search trick: site:book.hacktricks.xyz unifi
Good pages to bookmark:

https://book.hacktricks.xyz/linux-hardening/privilege-escalation
https://book.hacktricks.xyz/windows-hardening/windows-local-privilege-escalation
https://book.hacktricks.xyz/pentesting-web/file-inclusion

STEP 6 - CLONE RESOURCES LOCALLY FOR OFFLINE USE
git clone https://github.com/carlospolop/hacktricks
git clone https://github.com/swisskyrepo/PayloadsAllTheThings
Search them offline:
grep -r "unifi" hacktricks/ --include=".md"
grep -r "log4j" hacktricks/ --include=".md"
grep -r "lxd" hacktricks/ --include="*.md"

OSCP GENERAL ENUMERATION CHECKLIST
PORT SCANNING:
nmap -sV -sC -p- TARGET -o nmap_full.txt
rustscan -a TARGET -- -sV -sC
WEB ENUMERATION:
gobuster dir -u http://TARGET -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt -x php,html,txt
nikto -h http://TARGET
curl -I http://TARGET
curl -L http://TARGET/robots.txt
curl -L http://TARGET/sitemap.xml
IDENTIFY CMS:
wpscan --url http://TARGET --enumerate (WordPress)
droopescan scan drupal -u http://TARGET (Drupal)
joomscan -u http://TARGET (Joomla)

